review_blob: Really good stuff if you are into strong ales. Bourbon really comes thru and the hops are very present at the back end. Another good brew by stone.

Aged this for about a year and it turned out great. Rum overtones really shine through. Lots of "breadyness" and sweetness on the finish. Almost like honey bread with some dark fruits in there. Great brew by weyerbacher.
A very big beer. Mouthfeel is almost perfect. Great hops and huge punch with the 11%. You can definitely taste the booze. Overall this is a great beer.

Pours golden with a nice white head that leaves good lacing throughout the glass. Has a great bitterness to it with plenty of piney notes. If you are a fan of dank IPAs you should be happy with this one.

Poured from 32 oz can which was filled at brewery....pours a cloudy walnut color...nose is full of pine, very reminiscent of "best by" from stone....taste follows the nose, very bitter and piney....head stays throughout with nice lacing. Medium body with a small amount of carbonation. If you like a bitter/dank IPA, you should like this beer.

Poured from a bomber after letting it six for six months.....dark burgundy look with an off white fluffy head....smells of strong fruit and yeast....tastes of bitter cherries with some nice carbonation....notes of darker fruits definitely come through as the beer warms .  Overall a good double.
beer_name: Ommegang Game of Thrones #4 - Valar Morghulis

review_blob: Pours a hazy light brown, not much head on this beer, and no lacing to speak of. Smell is absolutely amazing....lots of pumpkin & nutmeg. Very sweet smell, and the taste is very sweet as well. ABV is very well hidden, if you like pumpkin pie, you will like this beer....possibly a bit too sweet, but all things considered a very good beer in my book.

Poured from a growler on 1-2-14....pours a golden color with a very nice off white head.  Head stays with you throughout, so you definitely get some nice lacing.   Smell of hops punching you in the face with lots of citrus.  Taste follows the nose, lots of hops and citrus up front with a nice piney bitterness to top it off.  Medium body with just the right amount of carbonation.  Little boozy, but what DIPA isn't?  Good beer.

Pours a nice golden color with white head that sticks around throughout.  Smell is yeasty with a bit of sweetness, picking up some nice fruit on the nose...banana and possibly some tart cherry?  Nice Belgian double taste with lots of  tart bitterness at the end.  Medium to light mouthfeel with good amount of carbonation.  Overall a good beer if you are a fan of Belgian beers.

Poured from a growler.....two days after brought back from bar. Pours dark with a nice kaki head and good lacing throughout. Nose is an incredible coffee smell along with some sweetness. Taste is strong coffee and chocolate leading to a nice bitter aftertaste. Very good beer, and one I will be trying again.

Pours a dark brown with a red hue. Roasty taste with a light body more carbonation than I expected. Nice change of pace for a winter ale, not a "big boy" beer by any means, but it's a good beer on a cold night.

From growler on Dec 26th....Nice hoppy and earthy nose....taste follows the nose.  Pours a hazy dark brown with nice head and good lacing throughout.  Not much carbonation, and very earthy mouthfeel, leaves you with a power full bitter aftertaste.  Not sure o the ABV, but overall good IPA.
Had in cellar for two years.....can really smell the pineapple. Little to no head, and no lacing at all. Picking up a lot of citrus and pin able in the taste....very interesting beer. Glad I had it.

Great nose....perfect body for a stout. The taste is a little boozy, but after aging it for a year it becomes absolutely amazing. Keeping yourself from drinking it and allowing this one to age is not the easiest thing to do.
Great nose. Very dank beer, hops about punch your face. Lacks a little body, but overall a good beer.
Sweet IPA....great lacing....good body. Once again 2014 is a good release.
Little light, and high on the carbonation, but the nose and taste are very good. Piney and citrus notes really come through on this one....troegs makes another good IPA.
Yeasty....little boozy, but very good quad.  Will cellar a few, I think if allowed to sit for a year or so it would be amazing.
